'''Christopher Robert Wellesley Grant''' (19 December 1935 – 22 October 2017)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thepca.co.uk/obituaries.html#Chris%20Grant |title=Chris Grant |access-date=13 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170622192424/http://www.thepca.co.uk/obituaries.html#Chris%20Grant |archive-date=22 June 2017 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> was an English [[cricket]]er active in the late 1960s. Born at [[Lincoln, England|Lincoln]], [[Lincolnshire]], Grant was a left-handed [[batsman (cricket)|batsman]]. He died at [[Newark-on-Trent]], [[Nottinghamshire]].

Grant made his debut in [[first-class cricket]] for [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire]] against [[Derbyshire County Cricket Club|Derbyshire]] in the [[1968 County Championship]], with him making two further first-class appearances in 1968 against the touring [[Australia national cricket team|Australians]] and [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/29/29738/First-Class_Matches.html|title=First-Class Matches played by Christopher Grant|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref> He scored 125 runs in his three matches, top-scoring with 48.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/29/29738/f_Batting_by_Team.html|title=First-class Batting and Fielding For Each Team by Christopher Grant|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref> He also made a single appearance in [[List A cricket]] in 1968, against [[Worcestershire County Cricket Club|Worcestershire]] in the [[1968 Gillette Cup|Gillette Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/29/29738/List_A_Matches.html|title=List A Matches played by Christopher Grant|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>

